Indian Stocks End Two-Day Rally on Europe; Software Makers Lead

-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-10-11T10:13:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/indian-stocks-end-two-day-rally-on-europe-software-makers-lead.html
Indian stocks dropped for the first
time in three days amid concern  Europe ’s debt crisis may worsen
and may hurt the profitability of local companies.  Infosys Ltd., the second-largest software exporter, paced
declines among peers as the European Central Bank President
Jean-Claude Trichet today said Europe’s debt crisis has reached
a “systemic dimension.”  India ’s biggest software makers earn
about three-quarters of their revenue from overseas. Sterlite
Industries (India) Ltd., the biggest copper producer, slid 1.7
percent.  Bharti Airtel Ltd. (BHARTI)  gained after the government said it
planned to make more spectrum available to operators and allow
sharing and trading of airwaves.  The BSE India Sensitive Index fell 38.51, or 0.2 percent,
to 16,518.72, according to preliminary closing prices at 3:30
p.m. Mumbai time. S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock
Exchange of India Ltd. dropped 0.1 percent to 4,974.35. Its
October futures traded at 4,980.10.  Overseas funds bought a net 4.91 billion rupees ($100
million) of Indian equities on Oct. 7, paring the outflow to
28.3 billion rupees, according to data on the  website  of the
Securities & Exchange Board of India. They withdrew a net $2.4
billion in August, the most since October 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
